Installing on Linux and other POSIX systems
===========================================

Prerequisites:

        - The Qt library, version 4.x.x
        - A C++ compiler
        - The source code; either unpack the source .tar.gz or do
          git clone git://github.com/bullestock/c45b.git

Compilation:

        
        cd c45b
        qmake-qt4
        make

Installation:

On Debian-based systems (including Ubuntu), I recommend
installing using

           sudo checkinstall --fstrans=no

Otherwise, simply do

           sudo install



Installing on Windows
=====================

Prerequisites:

        - The Qt library, version 4.x.x
        - A C++ compiler
        - The source code; either unpack the source ZIP file or do
          git clone git://github.com/bullestock/c45b.git

Compilation:

        qmake
        nmake (for Visual C++; for MinGW use 'make')
